FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE, CATTLE - ZAMBIA (03)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 26 Apr 2004
From: Wilna Vosloo <Wilna@saturn.ovi.ac.za>

Response to FMD in Zambia Digest 2004 #117: suspected FMD spreads in Zambia
-------------------------------------------
Clinical material (2 samples from mouth and 2 from foot lesions) was
submitted to the Exotic Diseases Division [EDD], Onderstepoort Veterinary
Institute, on 12 Mar 2004. It was stated that one sample was taken from
healed lesions.
No virus could be isolated on primary pig kidney cells from any of the
samples despite 2 blind passages. The polymerase chain reaction was
negative as well as the sandwich ELISA-detecting antigen. In order to
obtain a diagnosis, the Zambian authorities are urged to submit fresh
samples to the EDD for further testing.
--
Dr Wilna Vosloo
Head: Exotic Diseases Division
Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute
Private Bag X05
Onderstepoort 0110
South Africa
tel 27-12-5299592
